revision.text:
'''Basidiolichens''' are [[lichen]]ized members of the [[Basidiomycota]], a much smaller group of lichens than the far more common ascolichens in the [[Ascomycota]]. In arctic, alpine, and temperate forests, the most common basidiolichens are in the [[agaric]] [[genus]] ''[[Lichenomphalia]]''<ref name="urlLichenomphalia umbellifera. photo - cvcc photos at pbase.com">{{cite web |url=http://www.pbase.com/cvcc/image/58989351&gcmd=add_comment |title=''Lichenomphalia umbellifera''. photo - cvcc photos at pbase.com |format= |work= |accessdate=2009-01-12}}</ref> (including former members of ''[[Omphalina]]'' or ''[[Gerronema]]'') and the [[clavarioid]] genus ''[[Multiclavula]]''.<ref name="urlMulticlavula corynoides">{{cite web |url=http://www.lichen.com/bigpix/Mcorynoides.html |title=''Multiclavula corynoides'' |work= |accessdate=2009-01-12| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20081223041903/http://www.lichen.com/bigpix/Mcorynoides.html| archivedate= 23 December 2008 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref> Several lichenized genera occur in tropical regions, the most common being the foliose ''[[Dictyonema]]''. Previously basidiolichens had been classified in their own subclass, [[Wettstein system|Basidiolichenes]]. Molecular based [[phylogeny]] does not support classification of the genera together.
