'''Debasisa Mohanty''' (born 30 November 1966) is an Indian computational biologist, bioinformatician and a staff scientists at the [[National Institute of Immunology, India]]. Known for his studies on structure and function prediction of proteins, [[genome analysis]] and computer simulation of [[Biomolecule|biomolecular systems]], Mohanty is an elected fellow of all the three major Indian science academies namely the [[Indian Academy of Sciences]], the [[Indian National Science Academy]] and the [[National Academy of Sciences, India]]. The [[Department of Biotechnology]] of the Government of India awarded him the [[National Bioscience Award for Career Development]], one of the highest Indian science awards, for his contributions to biosciences, in 2009.

== Biography ==
[[File:A building at IIT Kanpur.jpg|thumb|left|IIT Kanpur]]
Born on 30 November 1966,<ref name="Fellow profile">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ias.ac.in/describe/fellow/Mohanty,_Dr_Debasisa |title=Fellow profile |date=2018-01-21 |publisher=Indian Academy of Sciences |access-date=2018-01-21}}</ref> Debasisa Mohanty earned a post graduate degree (MSc) in physics from the [[Indian Institute of Technology, Kanpur]] in 1988 and did his doctoral studies at the Molecular Biophysics Unit of the [[Indian Institute of Science]] to secure a PhD in computational biophysics in 1994.<ref name="About the speaker">{{Cite web |url=http://www.mecheng.iisc.ernet.in/~spapro/Dmohanty.htm |title=About the speaker |date=2018-01-21 |website=www.mecheng.iisc.ernet.in |access-date=2018-01-21}}</ref> Subsequently, he completed his post-doctoral work, first the [[Hebrew University of Jerusalem]] and, later, at the [[Scripps Research Institute]].<ref name="Debasisa  Mohanty on NII">{{Cite web |url=http://www.nii.res.in/research/debasisa-mohanty |title=Debasisa  Mohanty on NII |date=2018-01-21 |website=www.nii.res.in |access-date=2018-01-21}}</ref> On his return to India, he joined the [[National Institute of Immunology, India]] (NII) where he serves as a Grade IV staff scientist and hosts a number of research scholars at his laboratory. At NII, he also supervises the activities of ''RiPPMiner'', (Bioinformatics Resource for Deciphering Chemical Structures of RiPPs)<ref name="RiPPMiner">{{Cite web |url=http://www.nii.ac.in/~priyesh/lantipepDB/new_predictions/contactus.php |title=RiPPMiner |date=2018-01-21 |website=www.nii.ac.in |access-date=2018-01-21}}</ref> and the Bioinformatics Centre.<ref name="Bioinformatics Centre">{{Cite web |url=http://www.cosidici.com/INSTITUTES/NATIONAL%20INSTITUTE%20OF%20IMMUNOLOTY.htm |title=Bioinformatics Centre |date=2018-01-21 |website=Council Of State Industrial Development and Investment Corporations Of India (COSIDICI) |access-date=2018-01-21}}</ref>

Mohanty resides at the NII Campus, along [[Aruna Asaf Ali Marg]] in [[New Delhi]].<ref name="NASI fellows">{{Cite web |url=http://www.nasi.org.in/fellows.asp?RsFilter=M |title=NASI fellows |date=2018-01-21 |publisher=National Academy of Sciences, India |access-date=2018-01-21}}</ref>

== Legacy ==
[[File:Genome viewer screenshot small.png|thumb|A partially sequenced [[genome]].]]
Mohanty's research focus is in the fields of [[computational biology]] and [[bioinformatics]]<ref name="Indian fellow">{{Cite web |url=http://insaindia.res.in/detail/P13-1617 |title=Indian fellow |date=2018-01-21 |publisher=Indian National Science Academy |access-date=2018-01-21}}</ref> and he is known to have developed computational methods for predicting the substrate specificity of proteins as well as identified [[biosynthetic]] pathways.<ref name="About the speaker" /> His work has assisted in widening the understanding of the function of putative proteins in [[genomes]] and the ''[[protein interaction]] networks in newly sequenced genomes''.<ref name="Debasisa  Mohanty on NII" /> His studies have been documented by way of a number of articles<ref name="On Google Scholar">{{Cite web |url=https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=ivcDx2gAAAAJ |title=On Google Scholar |date=2018-01-20 |publisher=Google Scholar |access-date=2018-01-20}}</ref>{{Refn|group=note|Please see ''Selected bibliography'' section}} and [[ResearchGate]], an online repository of scientific articles has listed 108 of them.<ref name="On ResearchGate">{{Cite web |url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Debasisa_Mohanty |title=On ResearchGate |date=2018-01-20 |publisher=On ResearchGate |access-date=2018-01-20}}</ref>

Mohanty was a member of the national organizing committee of the ''International Conference in Bioinformatics (INCOB)'' held in 2006 in India
<ref name="INCOB 2006">{{Cite web |url=https://incob.apbionet.org/incob06/committee.html |title=INCOB 2006 |date=2018-01-21 |website=incob.apbionet.org |access-date=2018-01-21}}</ref> and has delivered invited speeches at various conferences which included the seminar series on ''Proteomics and bioinformatics'' of the [[Regional Centre for Biotechnology]] held in 2013,<ref name="Proteomics and bioinformatics">{{Cite web |url=http://www.rcb.res.in/upload/2013/Workshop2013_5.pdf |title=Proteomics and bioinformatics |date=2013 |website=Regional Centre for Biotechnology |access-date=2018-01-21}}</ref> the ''Symposium on Accelerating Biology 2017: Delivering Precision'' of the [[Centre for Development of Advanced Computing]] (C-DAC) held in January 2017 in Pune,<ref name="Accelerating Biology 2017: Delivering Precision">{{Cite web |url=https://cdac.in/index.aspx?id=pdf_SYMP2017_technical_programme_final |title=Accelerating Biology 2017: Delivering Precision |date=2018-01-21 |website=Centre for Development of Advanced Computing (C-DAC) |access-date=2018-01-21}}</ref> and the ''Symposium on Functional Genomics'' organized by the [[Indraprastha Institute of Information Technology]] in Delhi in December 2017.<ref name="CCB@IIIT-Delhi">{{Cite web |url=http://ccb.iiitd.ac.in/CCB-group-meeting.html |title=CCB@IIIT-Delhi |date=2018-01-21 |website=ccb.iiitd.ac.in |language=en |access-date=2018-01-21}}</ref>

== Awards and honors ==
Mohanty received the Samanta Chandrashekhar Award of the Orissa Bigyan Academy in 2005<ref name="Details of the Previous Winners">{{Cite web |url=http://www.orissabigyanacademy.nic.in/award_scs_prv_winner.html |title=Details of the Previous Winners |date=2018-01-21 |website=www.orissabigyanacademy.nic.in |access-date=2018-01-21}}</ref> and the Rajib Goyal Young Scientist Prize in Life Sciences of [[Kurukshetra University]] in 2007.<ref name="Rajib Goyal Young Scientist Prize">{{Cite web |url=http://kuk.ac.in/userfiles/file/news/goyal%20prize%202008.pdf |title=Rajib Goyal Young Scientist Prize |date=2018-01-21 |website=Kurukshetra University |access-date=2018-01-21}}</ref> The [[National Academy of Sciences, India]] elected him as a fellow the next year<ref name="NASI Year Book 2015">{{Cite web |url=http://www.nasi.org.in/Year%20Book%202015.pdf |title=NASI Year Book 2015 |date=2018-01-21 |publisher=National Academy of Sciences, India |access-date=2018-01-21}}</ref> and the [[Department of Biotechnology]] (DBT) of the Government of India awarded him the [[National Bioscience Award for Career Development]], one of the highest Indian science awards in 2009.<ref name="Awardees of National Bioscience Awards for Career Development">{{Cite web |url=http://dbtindia.nic.in/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/list_of_bioscience_awardees.pdf |title=Awardees of National Bioscience Awards for Career Development |date=2016 |publisher=Department of Biotechnology |access-date=2017-11-20}}</ref> He became an elected fellow of the [[Indian Academy of Sciences]] in 2012<ref name="Fellowship - Indian Academy of Sciences">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ias.ac.in/listing/fellows/M |title=Fellowship - Indian Academy of Sciences |date=2018-01-16 |website=www.ias.ac.in |language=en |access-date=2018-01-16}}</ref> and of the [[Indian National Science Academy]] in 2013.<ref name="INSA Year Book 2016">{{Cite web |url=http://www.insaindia.res.in/pdf/YearBook_2016.pdf |title=INSA Year Book 2016 |date=2018-01-